description:
The data for this image was acquired partially in 2017 and then later in 2019 from Class 4 Bortle skies, west and north of Milwaukee, WI.  In total:

L: 23@600s
R: 7@600s
G: 7@600s
B: 17@600s

Processed using PixInsight as a traditional image and then used Starnet++ which worked wonders to produce what you see here.  I was amazed at how much more dust and dark nebula was visible without the stars to distract your eye.

Equipment was as follows:
Stellarvue SVAT130 at f/5
Hypertuned Celestron CGEM DX mount
QSI690-wsg8 w/ Astrodon filters (autoguide camera was Lodestar X2)
Captured using Sequence Generator Pro and processed in PixInsight
title: Iris Starless Nebula
